One man has died after a fire broke out inside a car paint shop in Avoca, Durban North. Eyewitnesses said the man died after going inside the burning shop to save a woman. The woman is understood to be in a nearby hospital and recovering from smoke inhalation. Bruce de Gier, Divisional Commander of eThekwini Fire Department confirmed that one man had died. "We are not sure what the cause of the fire is at the moment. It started around 12.45 pm and it took three fire engines and 15 fireman to put it out," he said. By 2 pm, firefighters had already contained the fire. The impact of the damage is still being assessed but only two shops were affected by the fire. The paint shop was burned to the ground while the neighbouring shop, a motor vehicle spare parts store, was slightly damaged.